<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7420> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7420" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In RE On nos. 7 and 50, Münzer holds that the fine levied on M. Postumius (17), Tr. mil. c. p. 426, in 423 (Liv. 4.40.4 and 41.10) ended his public career and therefore precludes him from being identified with no. 50, above. On the trial and conviction, see Ogilvie, Comm. Livy 594-595.[174]" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/388> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #388" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.31.1; Diod. 12.80.1; Chr. 354 (Cosso et Fiso); Degrassi 96, 374f. Postumius and Quinctius served under the Dictator against Veii (Liv. 4.40.4, and 41.10). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 4." .
